III- Active tillering stage : 35-40 DAS

Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

2. C. S. H-6: This type is cooked in a period of 100-105 days. Its granules can be produced from 32-34 quintals and bitter 80-82 quintals per hectare. Its plants 160-170 cm Are almost high. Granules are small in size. The most suitable type of mixed crop method is. This is a drought resistant variety.

3. C. S. H-9: This type is prepared after cropping in a period of 105-110 days. The production of granules is about 33 quintals and bitter 95-100 q / ha. Is available till Its plants are 182 cm Are almost high. Its granular shape has a slightly larger glaucoma shiny. This is a drought resistant variety.

4. C. S. H-14: These varieties are cooked in a period of 95-100 days. Its granules produce production from 36 to 40 quintals per hectare and bitter 85-90 quintals. Its plants are 181 cm Are almost high. This type is suitable for lesser land.

5. C. S. H-18: The cultivation period of this type is 110 days and production of both 34.44 quintals / ha and bitter 120 to 130 quintals is produced.

KCCAns:
Method for Preperation of bordex pest 
1. Dissolve one kilogram of copper sulphate in 5 liter of water in plastic bucket.
2. Dissolve one kilogram of quick lime in 5 liter of water seperately in plastic bucket.
3. Both solution are mixed in one bucket same time.
4. If the prepare mixture is in acidic range, it can be brought to neutral or near alkaline condition by adding some more lime solution into the mixture. 
5. To test the neutrality of the mixture, dip a well polished knife or a sickle in the mixture for few minutes. If reddish deposit appears on the knife/sickle, it indicates the acidic nature of the mixture.

KCCAns: Before sowing or transplanting in the field it is necessary to treat the seed. First, put the seeds in salt solution. For this, in the 10 liters of water, 1.6 kg of normal salt is made and the seed is added in this solution. Heavy and healthy seeds will sit down and light seeds will float above. Remove the light seeds separately and remove heavy seeds sitting below and wash them with clean water two or three times and dry them in the shade. Treatment of seeds with mold and fungal medicines, there is no possibility of spreading fungi and bacterial diseases spreading through seeds. For this, sow the seeds by giving them 2 grams monosal or thyme and 2 grams of Baviston per kg gram seeds. KCCAns:
Vermi Compost Preparation Method:

To prepare the compost from the waste, the pieces of glass and metal pieces are separated properly and after this, a 10x4 ft platform is prepared to prepare the Vermi Compost up to 6 to 12 inches high. Two rubbish bricks are added above this platform and huts are made for shade above the platform. Dry fodder on the platform, manure 3-4 quintals of cow dung and 7-8 quintals of garbage (Garvage) Which gets irrigated by sapling for 10-15 days so that the temperature of the compost can be reduced. After this, 100 thousand square feet are left to the extent of 10 thousand earthworms. After leaving the ketchu, the stitches are covered with jute sacks, and they keep irrigation for 4 days so that 45-50 percent moisture is maintained. Keep in mind that due to excessive wetness the air will be blocked and the microbes and earthworms will not be able to die or work.

After 45 days irrigation is stopped and jute bags are removed. After removing the brood, the top manure dries and the earthworms go down in humidity. Then separate the dry Vermic compost of the above. After 4-5 days, the upper manure of the stitches is dried and the dry manure is separated from the top. Thus, the entire compost separates from the stitches in 3-4 times and the earthworms are left in the last, whose number In two months, the number of earthworms inserted is doubled, keep in mind that do not use gantry, spade or cranberries to remove manure from hand. The manure taken from the strains is dried in a shade and filtered in a shady place. The quantity of Vermi compost requires 100 grams, one kilogram of one year plants and 6-8 quintals per acre in the crop. Using Vermicum Wash, it would be good to have two exhaust drains on the platform to collect the worm wash.
